{"word":"G3011 - λειτουργός - leitourgós - li-toorg-os' - Minister","slug":"G3011","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">λειτουργός</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>leitourgós"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>li-toorg-os'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Minister"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BB;&#x03B5;&#x03B9;&#x03C4;&#x03BF;&#x03C5;&#x03C1;&#x03B3;&#x03BF;&#x0301;&#x03C2; - leitourgos</b> - <i>li-toorg-os'</i><p/>From a derivative of <a href=\"#/G2992\">G2992</a> and <a href=\"#/G2041\">G2041</a>; a <i>public servant</i>, that is, a <i>functionary</i> in the Temple or Gospel, or (generally) a <i>worshipper</i> (of God) or <i>benefactor</i> (of man): - minister (-ed)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3008\">G3008</a>, <a href=\"#/G3009\">G3009</a>, <a href=\"#/G3010\">G3010</a>"}]}